{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EnNgTG6nDX9Pra7VwUbJcw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup. I need to:\n\n1. Look at the current state of the cluster - what namespace it's running in, what pods exist\n2. Create a new StatefulSet with 2 data nodes that have a different allocation attribute (e.g., `tier: warm` vs existing `tier: hot`)\n3. Configure the new nodes to join the cluster\n4. Update the index `app-data` routing so shards relocate to the new nodes\n\nThe key details from the code:\n- Namespace: `elasticsearch`\n- Original StatefulSet: `es-cluster` (3 replicas, must stay at 3)\n- Original nodes have `node.attr.tier: hot` set\n- Index `app-data` currently has `index.routing.allocation.require.tier: hot` configured\n\nSo my approach is to create a separate ConfigMap for the warm-tier nodes, spin up a new StatefulSet called `es-cluster-warm` with 2 replicas that use this ConfigMap, and then update the index routing policy to allow shards to move to the new warm nodes. The new nodes will automatically discover and join the existing cluster.\n\nLet me first check what the current cluster state looks like.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4992,"cache_read_input_tokens":32790,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4992},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d052192b-e55b-4784-a08c-04ef122306c0","uuid":"7a47d4e4-62ce-4d63-a82d-ea87a23c0594","request_id":"req_011Cc5P6ckjset12uFK736iH"}
